A spokeswoman for Lidl UK however sought to reassure customers that the company have 'strict quality control' on their products.

She said: 'We can assure our customers of the strict quality control processes we have in place with our suppliers and we take these matters extremely seriously.

'We would ask that Ms Noble contacts Lidl UK in the first instance to arrange the return of the packaging and the foreign object so that we may begin all relevant investigations into this, along with our supplier.'

